      • filter

        List<AuditLogEntry> filter(List<AuditLogEntry> auditLogEntries,
                           String filterMasks)
        Filters a list of AuditLogEntries according to the given filterMask. If the filterMask is null, empty or ill-formatted, the original list will be returned. A filterMask must be of the following format: 
        
 FilterMask   := Value | Value,KeyValueList | KeyValueList
 KeyValueList := Property=Value | Property=Value,KeyValueList | Property={Options}Value | Property={Options}Value,KeyValueList
 Property     := firstname | lastname | username | mail | user | experiment | bucket | app | time | attr | before | after
 Value        := any value, may not contain commas (,) followed by a Property. If it starts with an escaped
                 dash (\-), the value is negated, thus shall not match.
 Options      := property specific options, see below.
        If the filter mask just contains a value, all fields are filtered by this value: If the value is prefixed by a dash, all matches are removed from the list, if it is not prefixed all entries which have no match are removed. The KeyValueList will be split by commas. The matching is then done as the global matching but on a per field basis. All rules have to be fulfilled to retain an entry in the returned list. Available special Options by Property
        • time: time can take a time zone offset of the format sign digit digit digit digit.Example: time={-0700}mar 14
        Examples:
        • searchValue would yield all entries which somewhere contain 'searchValue'.
        • username=jdoe,experiment=testexp,bucket=-b would yield all entries for users with names containing 'jdoe', experiments containing 'testexp' und buckets not containing 'b'.
        • \-3 would yield all entries for users with names containing '-3'.
        • -3 would yield all entries for users with names not containing '3'.
        • rapid,bucket=abc would yield all entries which somewhere contain 'rapid' and have buckets' labels containing 'abc'.
        • rapid,abc would yield all entries which somewhere contain 'rapid,abc'.
        • null searches for 'null'
        Parameters:
        auditLogEntries - the list to be filtered
        filterMasks - the filter mask
        Returns:
        a filtered list

      • sort

        List<AuditLogEntry> sort(List<AuditLogEntry> auditLogEntries,
                         String sortOrder)
        Sorts a list of AuditLogEntries according to the given sortOrder. If the sortOrder is null, empty or ill-formatted, the original list will be returned. A sortOrder must be of the following format: 
        
 SortOrder    := Property | PropertyList
 PropertyList := Property,SortOrder
 Property     := any AuditLogProperty, may be prefixed with -
        Sorting is done from left to right, sorting by the first supplied property and if there are ties the next property decides how to break them etc. If a field is prefixed by a dash this means descending order, otherwise ascending order is used. Examples:
        • -username,experiment will sort by users (username and userid) (descending) and for each user by experiment labels (ascending) to break ties
        • experiment,bucket will sort by experiments and then for each experiment by bucket
        Note that both, username and user will try to sort by username first, and if that doesn't work will resort to userIDs.
        Parameters:
        auditLogEntries - the list to be sorted
        sortOrder - the sort order
        Returns:
        a sorted list
        See Also:
        AuditLogProperty.keys()
